messages.content:
You are a data processor. Extract and map data from the input JSON.

COMPANY: Look for companyName, company, business_name, organization
CONTACT NAME: Look for fullName, contact_name, name, full_name, contactName
EMAIL: Look for email, contact_email, emailAddress, contactEmail
PHONE: Look for phone, contact_phone, phoneNumber, contactPhone
LINKEDIN: Look for linkedinProfileUrl, linkedin, linkedin_url, profileUrl
LOCATION: Look for location, address, city, location_city
ROLE: Look for linkedinJobTitle, role, contact_role, jobTitle, position
EMPLOYEE COUNT: Look for employee_count, employees, companySize, size
NOTES: Look for linkedinHeadline, notes, description, bio, summary

INDUSTRY MAPPING - CRITICAL:
- "Technology" → "software"
- "Healthcare" → "healthcare"
- "Manufacturing" → "manufacturing"
- "Retail" → "retail"
- "Financial Services" → "finance"
- "Consulting" → "consulting services"
- "Real Estate" → "real_estate"
- Anything else → "other"

TAGS: Extract from role/industry/location using ONLY: ceo, founder, vp, director, manager, construction, healthcare, technology, high_priority, responded, meeting_schedule, software, vp_of_marketing, los_angeles, finance, senior_director_of_sales, new_york, manufacturing, operations_manager, detroit, retail, education, consulting, real_estate, marketing, legal, hr, accounting, government, nonprofit, media, energy, transportation, hospitality, project_manager, phoenix, entertainment, producer, beverly_hills

LOCATION: Split city/state, use state abbreviations.

Return ONLY valid JSON. No explanations, no markdown, no code blocks. Start with { and end with }.

{
  "lead_id": "{{ULID}}",
  "source": "linkedin",
  "acquired_at": "{{ISO8601}}",
  "company": "",
  "domain": "",
  "industry": "",
  "employee_count": 0,
  "contact_full_name": "",
  "contact_role": "",
  "contact_email": "",
  "contact_phone": "",
  "contact_linkedin": "",
  "location_city": "",
  "location_state": "",
  "status": "new",
  "utm_list_id": "pb-run-2025-01-25-1320",
  "tags": [],
  "notes": ""
}
